

Four people were killed and 15 injured in a road accident in central Nepal on Sunday, local police office said.

The accident occurred when a passenger bus bound for Narayangarh from Pokhara skidded off the road and fell into Trishuli river on the Mugling-Narayangarh road section of Chitwan district, some 200 km west of Kathmandu, local police office said in a statement.

The mishap occurred when the bus tried to overtake a mini truck, the police noted.

The injured are undergoing treatment at the Mahendra Adarsha Hospital and College of Medical Sciences Teaching Hospital in Bharatpur, the police said, adding, the condition of three is serious.

